Within this example, we display a map centered on the "Leaning Tower of Pisa", Italy (<span id="options">longitude</span>: 10.396623 and <span id="options">latitude</span>: 43.723236) with a hight <span id="options">zoom</span> level(17).<br><br>
var m = new <a href="<?php echo $documentation_path;?>/WIND.html" target="_blank">WIND</a>.<a href="<?php echo $documentation_path;?>/WIND.Map.html" target="_blank">Map</a>('<span id="param">map</span>', {'<span id="options">top</span>': 50, '<span id="options">left</span>': 100, '<span id="options">width</span>': 600, '<span id="options">height</span>': 500,'<span id="options">longitude</span>':10.396623, '<span id="options">latitude</span>': 43.723236, '<span id="options">zoom</span>': 17, '<span id="options">draggable</span>': true, '<span id="options">resizable</span>' : true})<br><br>
Here we specify the initial <span id="options">height</span> ( 500px ) and <span id="options">width</span> ( 600px ) , the position (<span id="options">top</span>:100 <span id="options">left</span>:100) of the map.<br>
'<span id="options">draggable</span>': true means that the map can be dragged on the window.<br>
'<span id="options">resizable</span>' : true means that the size is changeable.